WEBVTT

00:00:02.662 --> 00:00:05.663
I want you to think
about the image that you see

00:00:05.704 --> 00:00:07.579
when I say one word:

00:00:07.621 --> 00:00:08.871
migrant.

00:00:10.788 --> 00:00:13.329
You may have pictured
a crowded boat in rough waters,

00:00:13.371 --> 00:00:15.496
people clinging
to the top of a freight train

00:00:15.496 --> 00:00:18.288
or crossing a desert
wearing worn-out shoes.

00:00:18.329 --> 00:00:20.538
This is what we see in the news cycle,

00:00:20.579 --> 00:00:24.163
24 hours, day after day,
story after story.

00:00:24.204 --> 00:00:29.121
People who are desperate, fleeing wars,
fleeing climate change, fleeing poverty.

00:00:29.163 --> 00:00:32.954
But in reality, most people
move for more common reasons: